[{"id":"FT553853","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<p>The American artist Jacob Lawrence painted the two works shown.</p>\n\n<p>Discuss the historical and social themes in his work. How does the artist use formal elements to construct narrative?&nbsp;</p>\n","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<img alt=\"A painting of African American migrants shows the migrants following a flock of migratory birds above. Their possessions are wrapped in bundles and carried on peoples' backs or shoulders. The crowd of almost a dozen suggests an entire family or perhaps several families. They are all on foot more like refugees fleeing an unhappy past.\n\" height=\"266\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/89c7edf99fd09ab833a9d68f46992ef9/original.jpg\" width=\"400\" />\n<p>Left</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"A painting shows a restaurant segregated between black and white patrons. The style of the figures and tables and place settings are all minimalists.  There is no food on any of the five tables and minimal cutlery. The faces of the white patrons are rendered with eyes, nose, mouths, but black patrons' faces are blank, non-persons. A gold cordon rope with posts divides the two groups who are only a few feet away from each other. \n\" height=\"448\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/83f1f13f945479f4b560ca7d51c63059/original.jpg\" width=\"300\" /></p>\n\n<p>Right</p>\n"}]}]